public class QueryTableView<R extends IBaseRow<?>> extends javafx.scene.control.TableView<R>
This extension of TableView directly associates a Query with the contents of a TableView, with potential support for editability.

  • Constructor Details

    • QueryTableView

      public QueryTableView(IBaseQuery<R> query, Boolean useKeyReplacement)
      This constructor uses Lambdas-as-InvalidationListeners and Dependables to tie the contents of the new QueryTableView into the results of the provided Query.
      Parameters:
      query - The query to display results from.
      useKeyReplacement - If true, replace Foreign Keys with readable ComboBoxes via TableKeyComboBoxCell and DivisionSelector cells.

    • constructTableColumnDependable

      private Dependable<javafx.collections.ObservableList<javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<R,?>>> constructTableColumnDependable(javafx.beans.value.ObservableValue<ResultSetMetaData> resultSetMetaDataObservableValue, javafx.collections.ObservableMap<String,Boolean> requestedColumnsObservableMap, Predicate<String> isColumnEditable)
      This method constructs a Dependable ObservableList of TableColumns, to update as the underlying query may update.
      Parameters:
      resultSetMetaDataObservableValue - The Observable Value of the metadata of the query to listen to.
      requestedColumnsObservableMap - The Observable Map of whether to display each column
      isColumnEditable - A test on the column name to determine if it should be editable
      Returns:
      a Dependable encapsulating an ObservableList of TableColumns, which can be passed into the TableView as Columns.

    • buildTableColumn

      private javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<R,?> buildTableColumn(int columnId, ResultSetMetaData md, String columnName, Boolean isPrimaryKey)
      This method constructs the requested Column. This method and some of its neighbors are really messy due to Java Generics.
      Parameters:
      columnId - The 1-indexed ID of the column in the ResultSet and ResultSetMetaData
      md - The ResultSetMetaData
      columnName - The name of the column to retrieve
      isPrimaryKey - Whether or not the column is a Primary Key
      Returns:
      A TableColumn which displays the requested Column in the ResultSet

    • _buildTableColumn

      private <V> javafx.scene.control.TableColumn<R,V> _buildTableColumn(int columnId, Class<V> columnClass, String columnName, String columnPrintableName, Boolean isPrimaryKey)
      Due to Java Generics, this method is the other half of buildTableColumn(int, java.sql.ResultSetMetaData, java.lang.String, java.lang.Boolean). This method constructs and assigns the attributes of the TableColumn.

      This mess builds the Callbacks which construct Cells. Because there are several Cell types, and Java generics can't be used for instantiation, this method is very stable but a lot more messy than I'd like.

      This mess is centrally dependent on constructing Lambdas which get implicitly typed as Callbacks for return.
